    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "0dc2f4c9",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "- **H0 (Null)**: Mean total sales are equal across all platforms\n",
        "- **H1 (Alternative)**: At least one platform has significantly different mean total sales than others"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "oLXTWrmUyCi5",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "oLXTWrmUyCi5"
      },
      "source": [
        "We use Levene’s test to evaluate whether the variance in total sales is similar across different platforms."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "9IdGrQ0bwjUj",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "9IdGrQ0bwjUj",
        "outputId": "48e6fd54-c6c6-4dd2-a9f3-7b8ab1f551ab"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "12.235899962251962 1.0801577776088078e-75\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from scipy.stats import levene\n",
        "\n",
        "# split data into platform groups\n",
        "groups = [g[\"total_sales\"].values for _, g in df.groupby(\"platform\")]\n",
        "\n",
        "# run Levene’s test for equal variances across platforms\n",
        "stat, p = levene(*groups)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "print(stat, p)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "n0U9yfaUyHrj",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "n0U9yfaUyHrj"
      },
      "source": [
        "ANOVA is used to test whether the average total sales differ across platforms. This helps determine if platform has a significant effect on game sales."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "ee8174dd",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "ee8174dd",
        "outputId": "a0349c85-ee19-499a-f7d1-a864767374ea"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "F-statistic: 25.22842607484863\n",
            "p-value: 1.3310069364243527e-132\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from scipy.stats import f_oneway\n",
        "\n",
        "groups = []\n",
        "\n",
        "# loop through each platform group\n",
        "for name, group in df.groupby(\"platform\"):\n",
        "    # keep only platforms with enough data points for reliable testing\n",
        "    if len(group) >= 5:\n",
        "        groups.append(group[\"total_sales\"].values)\n",
        "\n",
        "# perform one-way ANOVA across platform groups\n",
        "f_stat, p_val = f_oneway(*groups)\n",
        "\n",
        "# strength of differences between group means\n",
        "print(\"F-statistic:\", f_stat)\n",
        "\n",
        "# significance of those differences\n",
        "print(\"p-value:\", p_val)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "XFxWqvjEuCe-",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 1000
        },
        "id": "XFxWqvjEuCe-",
        "outputId": "8531aa59-e482-423c-d940-a112f8692714"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "image/png": "",
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1200x1200 with 1 Axes>"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "display_data"
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# function that groups each platform into a broader console family category\n",
        "def get_family(platform):\n",
        "    ps = [\"ps\", \"ps2\", \"ps3\", \"ps4\", \"psp\", \"psv\", \"psn\"]\n",
        "    xbox = [\"xb\", \"x360\", \"xone\", \"xbl\"]\n",
        "    nintendo = [\"nes\", \"snes\", \"n64\", \"gc\", \"wii\", \"wiiu\", \"ds\", \"3ds\", \"gb\", \"gba\", \"gbc\", \"ns\"]\n",
        "    pc = [\"pc\", \"osx\", \"linux\", \"mob\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "    if platform in ps:\n",
        "        return \"PlayStation\"\n",
        "    elif platform in xbox:\n",
        "        return \"Xbox\"\n",
        "    elif platform in nintendo:\n",
        "        return \"Nintendo\"\n",
        "    elif platform in pc:\n",
        "        return \"PC/Mobile\"\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        return \"Other\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# dictionary mapping each platform family to a plot color\n",
        "family_colors = {\n",
        "    \"PlayStation\": \"blue\",\n",
        "    \"Xbox\": \"green\",\n",
        "    \"Nintendo\": \"red\",\n",
        "    \"PC/Mobile\": \"purple\",\n",
        "    \"Other\": \"gray\"\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "# create a new column that assigns each platform to its family category\n",
        "df[\"family\"] = df[\"platform\"].apply(get_family)\n",
        "\n",
        "# recreate color mapping for plotting (redundant but used for visualization)\n",
        "family_colors = {\n",
        "    \"PlayStation\": \"blue\",\n",
        "    \"Xbox\": \"green\",\n",
        "    \"Nintendo\": \"red\",\n",
        "    \"PC/Mobile\": \"purple\",\n",
        "    \"Other\": \"gray\"\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12,12))\n",
        "\n",
        "for family, color in family_colors.items():\n",
        "    subset = df[df[\"family\"] == family]\n",
        "    plt.scatter(subset[\"platform\"], subset[\"total_sales\"],\n",
        "                label=family, alpha=0.4, color=color)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.xticks(rotation=90)\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Platform\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Total Sales (Millions)\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Total Sales by Platform Family\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
